{
  "name": "Switch Port",
  "type": "feat",
  "img": "icons/magic/control/fear-fright-white.webp",
  "system": {
    "description": {
      "value": "<p>Scout-Nin Keyword: Specialized</p><p>When you cast a jutsu that allows you to teleport or grants you and only you, a bonus to your movement speed, you can spend a superiority die and target an allied creature within 10 feet of you. </p><p>If the jutsu would teleport you, that creature teleports instead, and can add the superiority die to the next attack roll it makes before the end of its next turn. </p><p>If the jutsu would grant you a bonus to your movement speed, they gain the effects of the jutsu instead of you for its listed duration as if they had cast it. </p><p>If the jutsu requires concentration, you can choose if they or you will maintain concentration when this maneuver is used. </p><p>Once decided, you cannot change who is maintain concentration.</p>",
